Interface GGMultiTouchListener


  • public interface GGMultiTouchListener
    Declarations of the notification method called by multi-touch events.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean multiTouchEvent(GGMultiTouch multiTouch)
      Event callback method called when a screen mulit-touch event occurs.

    • Method Detail

      • multiTouchEvent

        boolean multiTouchEvent(GGMultiTouch multiTouch)
        Event callback method called when a screen mulit-touch event occurs. Drag events are not cached, so if this callback method does not return fast enough, some drag events may get lost, but other event types are always reported.
        Parameters:
        multiTouch - the multiTouch reference to get information about the event
        Returns:
        true, if the event is consumed, so following listeners in the GGMultiTouchListener sequence will not get the event
